Common incorrect uses of `<{{componentName}}>`. Each entry pairs the wrong form with the right one and a one-line reason. System-wide rules live in [`docs/COMPONENTS.md`](../../../../../../docs/COMPONENTS.md#system-level-anti-patterns) - they apply here too but are not repeated.

## 1. <!-- imperative title, e.g. "Do Not Slot HTML Elements" -->

<!-- One sentence: WHY this is wrong (what breaks, a11y, framework semantics). -->

```html
<!-- 🚫 INCORRECT -->
<{{componentName}}><!-- the wrong usage --></{{componentName}}>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT -->
<{{componentName}}><!-- the right usage --></{{componentName}}>
```

## 2. <!-- imperative title -->

<!-- One sentence: WHY this is wrong. -->

```html
<!-- 🚫 INCORRECT -->
<{{componentName}}></{{componentName}}>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT -->
<{{componentName}}></{{componentName}}>
```

